<subSubSection id="C3616545FFC7FF87FFB8165FFCD5FCF3" pageId="7" pageNumber="594" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC436CEFFC7FF87FFB8165FFCD5FCF3" blockId="7.[113,1089,815,1128]" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFC7FF87FFB8165FFF3EFCD3" bold="true" box="[113,224,815,839]" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">Remarks.</emphasis>
This specimen differs from the African 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D4DFFC7FF87FD421640FCCAFCD3" authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1913" baseAuthorityName="Pic" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[651,788,816,839]" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" genus="Macrosiagon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="594" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bequaerti">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFC7FF87FD421640FD7FFCD3" box="[651,673,816,839]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFC7FF87FD671640FCCAFCD3" box="[686,788,816,839]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">bequaerti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
only by the non-transparent elytra without lighter whitish coloration in their posterior half.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3616545FFC7FF87FFB8161FFBFAFBF3" pageId="7" pageNumber="594" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BC436CEFFC7FF87FFB8161FFBFAFBF3" blockId="7.[113,1089,815,1128]" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFC7FF87FFB8161FFEDAFC13" bold="true" box="[113,260,879,903]" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">Distribution.</emphasis>
Three 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D4DFFC7FF87FE861600FDEEFC13" box="[335,560,879,903]" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" genus="Macrosiagon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="594" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFC7FF87FE861600FE02FC13" box="[335,476,880,903]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">Macrosiagon</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D4DFFC7FF87FD891600FD08FC13" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1801" box="[576,726,880,903]" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" genus="Macrosiagon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="594" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bipunctata">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFC7FF87FD891600FD88FC13" box="[576,598,880,903]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFC7FF87FDAD1600FD08FC13" box="[612,726,880,903]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">bipunctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D4DFFC7FF87FD2D1600FCA6FC13" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[740,888,880,903]" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" genus="Macrosiagon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="594" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferruginea">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFC7FF87FD2D1600FD24FC13" box="[740,762,880,903]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFC7FF87FCCE1600FCA6FC13" box="[775,888,880,903]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">ferruginea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D4DFFC7FF87FC651600FBE6FC13" baseAuthorityName="Laporte" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[940,1080,880,903]" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" genus="Macrosiagon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="594" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="terminata">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFC7FF87FC651600FC1CFC13" box="[940,962,880,903]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFC7FF87FC191600FBE6FC13" box="[976,1080,880,903]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">terminata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) are widespread in the Afrotropical Region and go through the southern part of the Arabian Peninsula to the Indian subcontinent or even further to the east and west. All three species show slight morphological or color variability in different areas (probably because of different ecological conditions). One can conclude that the Afrotropical 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D4DFFC7FF87FCD51680FC79FB93" authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1913" baseAuthorityName="Pic" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[796,935,1008,1031]" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" genus="Macrosiagon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="594" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bequaerti">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFC7FF87FCD51680FCECFB93" box="[796,818,1008,1031]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFC7FF87FC881680FC79FB93" box="[833,935,1008,1031]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">bequaerti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may have the same 
<typeStatus id="54C0886CFFC7FF87FF671160FF02FBBC" box="[174,220,1040,1064]" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">type</typeStatus>
of distribution, but there is no record of this species from the Arabian Peninsula so far. Such a disjunct distribution may indicate that the Indian specimen belongs possibly to a new species sister to 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D4DFFC7FF87FE9B1120FE02FBF3" authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1913" baseAuthorityName="Pic" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[338,476,1104,1127]" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" genus="Macrosiagon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="594" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bequaerti">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFC7FF87FE9B1120FEB6FBF3" box="[338,360,1104,1127]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFC7FF87FEBF1120FE02FBF3" box="[374,476,1104,1127]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">bequaerti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. More material is necessary to make a sound decision.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
